page.title: 01THE VILLAGE ENGLEFIELD GREEN
page.content: Englefield Green is partly an old village and was built in the 1870's and houses built since 1950 onwards. It is 20 miles from London and is surrounded by woodland and fields. There are three schools they are the County first school,ST Cuthbert's Primary and ST Jude's middle C/E.The nearest station is Egham which is about one and a half miles away London is about 30 minutes and Ascot is about 20 minutes.There is Royal Holloway College with Bedford Brunel College and Shoreditch Campus.There are mostly small shops in ST Jude's Rd Victoria Street and Bond Street.There are four churches,ST Judes C/E,the Catholic church,The Methodist church and The Elim church. There is a youth club in Corby Drive. There are three bus routes and they are 725,441 and 718.
